`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The project strictly separates `game/` (ECS logic) from `components/` (R3F rendering). Entity creation data (like `resolveEmissiveColor`) must live in `game/` so `ChunkManager` can import it without a bad cross-layer dependency.
- `GrovekeeperSpiritComponent` is already defined in `game/ecs/components/procedural/spirits.ts` and `grovekeeperSpiritsQuery` is already in `world.ts` — the infrastructure is ready; we just need the rendering component and ChunkManager wiring.
- Spirit pulse params (pulseSpeed, pulsePhase) aren't stored in the ECS component, so they should be derived from `spiritId` via a stable hash — the same pattern used elsewhere for seeded variation without additional stored fields.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

