`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `useMemo([spirit.spiritId])` pattern is ideal for deriving stable non-stored animation params (pulseSpeed, pulsePhase) from entity identity — computes once on mount, zero re-renders unless the entity is replaced.
- Wiring ChunkManager to call `generateLabyrinth` also adds hedge walls and decorations — these were previously generated by the pure function but never inserted into ECS. The spirit story was the natural trigger for completing the maze-to-ECS pipeline.
